%N A397484 Decimal encoding of the 92 positions of the main beam "regulator" and the two wings "indicators" in the Chappe telegraph code.
%C A397484 The angular positions of the regulator, which could be vertical or horizontal, and the angular positions of the two indicator wings, which are multiples of Pi/4, are converted into a 3 digit code of digits 1 to 8, using the following diagram:
%C A397484 .
%C A397484        5
%C A397484     6  |  4
%C A397484      \   /
%C A397484   7_      _ 3
%C A397484      /   \
%C A397484     8  |  2
%C A397484        1
%C A397484 The first digit gives the orientation of the regulator, 1 for vertical and 3 for horizontal. Digits two and three encode the absolute angular positions of the lower and upper indicator for a vertical regulator and of the right and left indicator for a horizontal regulator. Indicator positions extending the regulator are not used. 6 of the remaining 2*7*7=98 combinations were used for special indications.
%H A397484 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="/A397484/b397484.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..92</a>
%H A397484 J-M. Dilhac, <a href="https://ethw-images.s3.us-east-va.perf.cloud.ovh.us/ethw/1/17/Dilhac.pdf">The telegraph of Claude Chappe - an optical telecommunication network for the XVIIIth century</a>.
%H A397484 Montmartre secret, <a href="https://www.montmartre-secret.com/article-montmartre-telegraphe-chappe-120420350.html">Montmartre. Télégraphe Chappe</a>, 2013 (in French).
